{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "For example, IoT-enabled precision irrigation systems have demonstrated the potential to reduce water consumption by 30% while improving crop yields, showcasing the dual benefits of efficiency and sustainability (Hamdi et al. 2021; Nawandar and Satpute 2019).",
    "Beyond operational efficiency, IoT technologies integrate machine learning, artificial intelligence, and big data to provide actionable insights, allowing real-time control of farming operations and strategic planning for future challenges (Goedde et al. 2020; Wolfert et al. 2017).",
    "The economic impact of IoT in agriculture is equally transformative.",
    "IoT-driven advancements in connectivity and automation could contribute an estimated $350 billion in value to global food production by 2025 without requiring additional labor or resource inputs (Goedde et al. 2020; Monge et al. 2022).",
    "Automated farming systems enabled by IoT reduce costs and improve resource allocation, supporting economic and environmental sustainability in regions heavily dependent on agriculture, such as India (Jaison et al. 2023; Seetha et al. 2023; Singh et al. 2023a, b)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
